capacity.title: Capacity
capacity.description: Instantiates these much elements on initialize

schema.name: event
schema.title: Trigger Event
schema.description: Play tween on the specified event name. This event must be fired on the global application object (e.g. this.app.fire('eventname');).

schema.name: path
schema.title: Path
schema.description: The path from the entity to the property. e.g. 'light.color', 'camera.fov' or 'script.vehicle.speed'.

schema.name: relative
schema.title: Relative
schema.description: If checked, the start value is ingored and the end value will be the relative offset from the property's current value.

schema.name: duration
schema.title: Duration
schema.description: Time to execute the tween in milliseconds. Defaults to 1000.

schema.name: delay
schema.title: Delay
schema.description: Time to wait in milliseconds after receiving the trigger event before executing the tween. Defaults to 0.

schema.name: repeat
schema.title: Repeat
schema.description: The number of times the tween should be repeated after the initial playback. Defaults to 0.

schema.name: repeatDelay
schema.title: Repeat Delay
schema.description: Time to wait in milliseconds before executing each repeat of the tween. Defaults to 0.

schema.name: yoyo
schema.title: Yoyo
schema.description: This function only has effect if used along with repeat. When active, the behaviour of the tween will be like a yoyo, i.e. it will bounce to and from the start and end values, instead of just repeating the same sequence from the beginning. Defaults to false.

schema.name: startEvent
schema.title: Start Event
schema.description: Executed right before the tween starts animating, after any delay time specified by the delay method. This will be executed only once per tween, i.e. it will not be run when the tween is repeated via repeat(). It is great for synchronising to other events or triggering actions you want to happen when a tween starts.

schema.name: stopEvent
schema.title: Stop Event
schema.description: Executed when a tween is explicitly stopped via stop(), but not when it is completed normally.

schema.name: updateEvent
schema.title: Update Event
schema.description: Executed each time the tween is updated, after the values have been actually updated.

schema.name: completeEvent
schema.title: Complete Event
schema.description: Executed when a tween is finished normally (i.e. not stopped).

schema.name: repeatEvent
schema.title: Repeat Event
schema.description: Executed whenever a tween has just finished one repetition and will begin another.

orbitSensitivity.title: Orbit Sensitivity
orbitSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves around the orbit. Higher is faster

inertiaFactor.title: Inertia Factor
inertiaFactor.description: 0 for no inertia, higher numbers mean more inertia

labelTxt.title: Button Label
labelTxt.description: Call setText Function to set value of this text

schema.name: animValue
schema.description: x: min animValue | y: base animValue | z: max animValue

schema.name: delegate
schema.description: If no delegate is given, entity having this script will be animated. Otherwise delegate will be animated.

schema.name: animValue
schema.description: x: min animValue | y: base animValue | z: max animValue

schema.description: Assign delegate to change this.entity Image to deligate Image.

doubleTapSpeed.description: If value is 0 simple click will be used

m_luckHumanWithWhiteToothpaste.description: Luck to have Human with toothpaste between 0 and 1. --- 0.5 = 50% luck

m_luckZombieWithShit.title: Luck Zombie with shit
m_luckZombieWithShit.description: Luck to have Zombie with shit between 0 and 1. --- 0.5 = 50% luck

m_luckHeadWithObstacle.title: Luck Head with Obstacle
m_luckHeadWithObstacle.description: Luck to have Head instead of obstacle between 0 and 1. --- 0.5 = 50% luck

frustumCulling.title: Frustum Culling
frustumCulling.description: Controls the culling of instances against the camera frustum (frustum culling needs to enabled on each camera component). If false all instances will be rendered regardless of their visibility. Changing this setting requires application reload.

cloneMaterials.title: Clone Materials
cloneMaterials.description: If selected all instances will use a clone of the original model material. This is useful when the original material is being used in non instanced models and otherwise it will produce render artifacts. Changing this setting requires application reload.

disableShadows.title: Disable Shadows
disableShadows.description: If selected no shadows buffers will be created (optimization). Requires app reload.

excludeTag.title: Exclude Tag
excludeTag.description: The tag that can be used on entities to exclude them from instancing.

excludeLayers.title: Exclude Layers
excludeLayers.description: Mesh instances rendered in these layers won't be instanced.

disableTransparent.title: Disable Transparent
disableTransparent.description: If selected transparent mesh instances will not be instanced.

autoUpdate.title: Auto Update
autoUpdate.description: Run the instancer update method automatically per frame. If Frustum Culling is selected this property doesn't have any effect.

bodyBackgroundColor.title: Body Background Color
bodyBackgroundColor.description: Background color of body element (where the banner should be displayed). Make sure the checkbox above is checked!

debugConfig.title: Debug / Testing Mode
debugConfig.description: Force safe areas to be applied to the UI. Useful testing layouts without a device.

resizeOnInput.title: Resize when input received
resizeOnInput.description: Resize the canvas every time an input event is received? This may help if the game reports incorrect input positions due to Famobi offsets but may cause slight CPU overhead in some games.
